Simplifying Function Tracing for the Modern GCC

   Zack Brown - July 26, 2019
   Steven Rostedt wanted to do a little housekeeping, specifically with
   the function tracing code used in debugging the kernel. Up until then,
   the kernel could enable function tracing using either GCC's -pg flag or
   a combination of -pg and -mfentry. In each case, GCC would create a
   special routine that would execute at the start of each function, so
   the kernel could track calls to all functions.

